Cape Town – Four people were killed and two seriously injured following a head-on collision between two vehicles on the R43 between Gansbaai and Pearly Peach in the Overberg on Friday. Western Cape Traffic chief Kenny Africa said the road – between Uilenkraalsmond and Pearly Beach – has been closed to traffic in both directions at the scene. “In this crash, several people lost their lives and another two seriously injured and awaits the helicopters to come and take them to the nearest hospital. The road is currently closed for traffic and we ask motorists to please be patient.” Images from the tragic scene show multiple bodies lying across the highway, with both vehicles severely damaged.     Cape Times